HEADWORD: Water battery
<hw>Wa"ter bat"ter*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld>
<def>A voltaic battery in which the exciting fluid is water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A battery nearly on a level with
the water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water bear</ent>⟦br⟧
